race.comment: The consistent WINCHMAN (2) got the job done around this circuit two back before just running into one better at Dalby last time out. Gets plenty of weight off with the 3kg claim and is drawn ideally in gate two. Looks the one they all have to run down. Former Victorian NUTS 'N' BOLTS (4) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this company easier than what he has been facing down south. Respect any push in betting. DRIALLE (1) is first-up here but looked to have come back in good order with a recent trial victory and may run a big race while fresh. LOADED GUN (3) rounds out the selections.
